
# Cross-Subject Music-Emotion Prediction: Project README

## Project Overview

This project investigates the generalizability of machine learning models for predicting music-induced emotions from EEG and acoustic features, using the OpenNeuro ds002721 dataset. Unlike prior work that focused on within-subject validation (which can overfit to individual brain signatures), we implement a **Leave-One-Subject-Out (LOSO)** cross-validation strategy to benchmark real-world, zero-calibration performance for unseen users.

**Key Goals:**
- Bridge the gap between "lab-accurate" and deployable models for neurotechnology and music-therapy applications.
- Prevent data leakage by ensuring models are never trained and tested on the same subject.
- Compare interpretable (Lasso), robust (Random Forest), and state-of-the-art (XGBoost) regression models.

## Dataset

- **Source:** [OpenNeuro ds002721](https://openneuro.org/datasets/ds002721) (Daly et al., 2015)
- **Subjects:** 31 healthy adults, 6 runs each (resting state + music listening)
- **EEG:** 19 channels, 1000 Hz, BIDS format, ~3.6 GB EDF files
- **Stimuli:** 40 film soundtrack clips (Eerola & Vuoskoski, 2010, Set 1)
- **Emotion Ratings:** 8 Likert scales per clip, mapped to Valence/Energy/Tension via PCA
- **Audio Features:** 360 MP3s, MFCCs, Chroma, BPM, etc.

## Methodology

### Validation: Leave-One-Subject-Out (LOSO)
For $N$ subjects, train on $N-1$ and test on the $N^{th}$ subject. Repeat for all subjects. This prevents the model from memorizing individual EEG baselines and tests true generalizability.

### Models Compared
- **Lasso Regression:** Interpretable, automatic feature selection (Krish, 2021)
- **Random Forest:** Robust to artifacts/outliers
- **XGBoost:** State-of-the-art for tabular data

### Feature Engineering
- **EEG:** Band power, Hjorth parameters, DWT features
- **Audio:** MFCCs, Chroma, BPM, Key, etc.
- **Combined:** All features concatenated for multimodal prediction

## Project Structure

```
daly-comp-analysis/
├── notebooks/                  # 01_eda_raw_data to 05_model_xgboost
├── src/                       # eeg_utils, audio_utils, features, models, viz
├── data/                      # features/, models/, results/ (git-ignored)
